Quiggles
Havre, MT14 contributions
Human version of IKEA
Aug 2024 • Friends
First, I can't say I was super interested in this exhibit. The family wanted to go, so we did - turns out it was very interesting!

It was interesting. If you think you might be interested in how we work, this is for you. These are REAL bodies. They do ask you to be respectful, which is fair. A lot of information. There is a reproductive area, but if you think this is not something you can do, they offer a place to go around it.

There are a few pieces that are veins and vessels that were injected with some type of polymer. So what you are looking at is a web showing circulation, and it sounds odd to say this, but they were beautiful. The arm shows how much circulation there is in your fingertips - who knew!
